crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_msg: POLICY-OTHER HTTP request by IPv4 address attempt

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered downloader. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

attributes.magic: POSIX shell script, ASCII text executable

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The script modifies the PATH environment variable. It then downloads two files, "112" and "112s", from the URL `http://43.249.172.195:888/` using both `wget` and `curl`.  The script makes both files executable and executes them. Finally, it removes the downloaded files and clears the shell history.
